Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteInstPad(25.10)                                      deleteInstPad(25.10)

Name
       deleteInstPad - Deletes the padding for the specified instances, or all
       instance-based padding, in the design

Syntax
       deleteInstPad

       [<instName>| -all]

       -suppress

       Deletes  the padding for the specified instances, or all instance-based
       padding, in the design.

Parameters
       <instName>
              Deletes the padding on the specified instance.

       -all   Deletes all instance-based padding.

       -suppress
              Suppresses verbose messages. The option is of type  boolean  and
              is optional.

Examples
              * The following command deletes padding for all instances in the
                design:

                deleteInstPad -all

                It outputs following:

                Delete Padding for Instant [U27312].

                Delete Padding for Instant [U27313].

                Delete Padding for Instant [U27314].

                Delete Padding for Instant [U27315].

                16432

              * The  following command deletes padding for one instances named
                U27316:

                deleteInstPad U27316

                It outputs following:

                Delete Padding for Instant [U27316].

       Note:  deleteInstPad deletes padding for either all instances or single
       instance. Wildcard is not supported yet.

